
Aim: To implement Hash Table.
Program: Write a Program to implement Hash Table with open addressing (Linear Probing) using a List.
	Test with:
	Insert keys [12, 44, 13, 88, 23] 
	Search 44 
	Delete 13.
Description:
Hash Table with Linear Probing
This program implements a Hash Table in Python using open addressing with linear probing for collision handling. The HashTable class provides:
•	Hash function: Computes index using modulo operation (key % table_size)
•	Insert: Places key at hashed index; if occupied, linearly probes to find the next available slot
•	Search: Looks up key by checking hashed index and probing forward until key is found or empty slot is reached
•	Delete: Marks deleted positions with a special marker to maintain probe sequence integrity
•	Linear probing: Resolves collisions by checking next consecutive slots: (hash + 1) % size, (hash + 2) % size, etc.
The program is tested with a table size of 10. Keys [12, 44, 13, 88, 23] are inserted (with collisions resolved via linear probing), key 44 is successfully searched, and key 13 is deleted while maintaining the hash table structure.






Code:
print("P.Manoj cse-c 24241")
class HashTable:
    
    def __init__(self, size):
        self.size = size
        self.table = [None] * size

    def hash_func(self, key):
        return key % self.size

    def insert(self, key):
        index = self.hash_func(key)
        start = index
        while self.table[index] is not None:
            index = (index + 1) % self.size
            if index == start:
                print("Hash table is full!")
                return
        self.table[index] = key
        print(f"Inserted {key} at index {index}")

    def search(self, key):
        index = self.hash_func(key)
        start = index
        while self.table[index] is not None:
            if self.table[index] == key:
                print(f"Key {key} found at index {index}")
                return True
            index = (index + 1) % self.size
            if index == start:
                break
        print(f"Key {key} not found")
        return False

    def delete(self, key):
        index = self.hash_func(key)
        start = index
        while self.table[index] is not None:
            if self.table[index] == key:
                print(f"Deleted {key} from index {index}")
                self.table[index] = None
                return
            index = (index + 1) % self.size
            if index == start:
                break
        print(f"Key {key} not found to delete")

    def display(self):
        print("Hash Table:", self.table)

# ----- Main Program -----
size = int(input("Enter hash table size: "))
ht = HashTable(size)

n = int(input("Enter number of keys to insert: "))
for _ in range(n):
    key = int(input("Enter key: "))
    ht.insert(key)

ht.display()

# Search key
key = int(input("\nEnter key to search: "))
ht.search(key)

# Delete key
key = int(input("\nEnter key to delete: "))
ht.delete(key)

ht.display()
